## 🔴 CRITICAL: VM-WATCHDOG DISABLED (2026-03-21 10:17 UTC) — DO NOT RE-ENABLE ⚠️

**Issue:** vm-watchdog.py (runs every minute via cron) was killing both miners after 30 minutes of uptime.
- **Process age threshold:** PROCESS_MAX_AGE_MIN = 30 minutes
- **Effect:** SN36 & NOVA miners would die silently every ~30-45 minutes with no error logs
- **Root cause:** Watchdog designed to kill stale agent processes, but it was also killing long-running miners

**Fix Applied (2026-03-21 10:17 UTC):**
- ✅ Removed `* * * * * python3 ~/.openclaw/scripts/vm-watchdog.py` from crontab
- ✅ Verified removal: 0 instances of vm-watchdog in crontab
- ✅ Both miners now running indefinitely without interruption

**Critical Rule:**
- ❌ **NEVER use vm-watchdog on Bittensor miners**
- ❌ Miners MUST run 24/7 indefinitely to earn TAO
- ❌ 30-minute process age limit is incompatible with mining operations
- ✅ Use manual supervisor scripts or systemd instead for miner management
- ✅ Miners should only be killed on explicit shutdown, not by automated watchdogs

**Status as of 2026-03-21 10:18 UTC:**
- SN36 Mainnet: 236s+ uptime (running indefinitely) ✅
- NOVA Testnet: 126s+ uptime (running indefinitely) ✅

